<PowerShell script that uses Microsoft.Graph.Authentication, supports AuthMode Interactive|Certificate, parameters TenantId, ClientId, CertificateThumbprint/CertificatePath/CertificatePassword, uses Connect-MgGraph accordingly, uses invite endpoint with sendInvitation=false and requireSignIn=true, reads CSV with columns Owner Login, Path, Item Name, Collaborator Login, Collaborator Permission, maps Box roles to Graph roles read/write or skip, resolves user drive with Get-MgUser and Get-MgUserDrive, resolves item by path using Invoke-MgGraphRequest GET /drives/{driveId}/root:/{path}, invites recipient via POST /drives/{driveId}/items/{itemId}/invite, supports ShouldProcess WhatIf/Confirm, logs to LogFolder, outputs PSCustomObject per row with status/error>